runs.comm: lets the opening ball go outside off
moves across his stumps and flicks nicely through midwicket past the inner ring
comes down the track and blazes a cut away over the point fielder and past the deep third man to the fence
punches off the back foot into the covers
tries to advance again but almost yorks himself, manages to adjust to the slower ball and dig it out past the bowler
defends a ball outside off but can't get the placement right
angling across the right-hander who lets it pass him by
comes down and slapped back past the bowler but it cannons into the stumps with the non-striker well out of the crease, luckily for him Bates couldn't get a hand to it
stays back and pushes to the left of the mid-off fielder
accurate good length ball on middle and off which gives the batsman little option but to defend down the pitch
fires this too wide of off past the flailing cut
tucks this off the pads through square leg
comes down and tries to swing into the leg side, misses completely and it seams past leg stump
comes down and defends into the point region and quickly sets off
tries to heave a short ball away into the leg side but misses and it hits him on the body
full on middle and leg and he flicks with some power past the diving Hira at mid-on
very poor delivery, friendly half-volley on leg and Hamilton picks it up and sends it sailing over square leg onto the roof of the makeshift bar at the ground
came down and sliced a heave just over a leaping point fielder, the man in the deep flicks it past his helper and they get the opportunity to sneak another run
shuffles across and works it away from mid-on who has to run round
interesting stroke to a short ball angling across, Matsikenyeri slams it back over Bates' head into the sightscreen on the full
short ball down leg, moves across and pulls over the fine leg boundary, the tourists off to a rollicking start
played into the deep at cow corner, is sent back after wanting the second
slower ball at 121kph is tucked off the pads to fine leg on the edge of the circle
and is promptly dispatched to the long-on boundary, full on the stumps and flicked past mid-on who gave up the chase quickly
defends into the off side
cramped for room and squeezes it into the leg side
beautifully timed, too full on the stumps again and he gets the feet out of the way to drive cleanly through the line along the ground back past the bowler
smacks a full ball back down the pitch, Southee gets a hand to it and deflects it to mid-on as they bring up Zimbabwe's first 50 opening stand of the tour
can't get enough wrist behind the whip to leg and finds mid-on
short on middle and mistimes the heave on the bounce to long-on
full toss and is fortunate to only concede the single as the slog finds long-on on the bounce
gets down on one knee and slog-sweeps beautifully with both elevation and distance over the cow corner boundary
works this straight to mid-on and the non-striker has to scramble back
Zimbabwe dominating the hosts now, haven't said that too many times on this tour, another full toss and Hamilton takes full toll and smashes it well back over the midwicket boundary
punched firmly to mid-off where Franklin fumbles and gives away the single
worked into the leg side
gets underneath a full ball and doesn't completely get hold of it but gets it wide of long-on on the bounce
straight back over the bowler's head, he made to swipe through the leg side and ended up lofting with a horizontal bat over the rope
fired in on middle and leg, cramped for room and defends back
New Zealand finally break through after a brilliant start by Zimbabwe, Stuart couldn't get enough on this smash down the ground and picked out long-off but he has more than played his part
defends with an open face behind point and after much stuttering, they make it through
defends down the pitch solidly
squeezes a full ball outside off through the covers into the deep
brings up his second consecutive half-century with an emphatic pull to a gentle short ball on the stumps, sends it packing over midwicket
hits into the covers where Nathan McCullum dives well to save a boundary
stays in the crease and defends solidly
very full ball swinging into Hamilton, he falls over and there is a loud appeal for lbw, umpire isn't sure if it is bat or pad first, looks like pad on the replays
tries to work the single but gets tangled up and can only defend back down the pitch
defends nicely into the off side and they set off quickly
banged in short and Masakadza tries to upper-cut over the slips but can't connect, Baz can't take it cleanly and they sneak a bye
comes down the track and lofts over the bowler's head, that shot was all about precise timing rather than power
worked into the leg side
comes down and converts it into a full toss, flicked to long-on
again comes down and gives a bit of room this time to chip over cover to the left of long-off
can't get the drive past the bowler who rushes across to stop it
pushes this down to long-off to end an excellent opening 10 overs from Zimbabwe who should be looking for 200 here
gets forward and waits before defending into the off side with soft hands
goes back and works to long-on to bring up the 100, they steal another run as the return throw hits the stumps and heads off in a direction of its own making
goes back and cuts through the covers
comes down the track and heaves a ball outside off across the line without timing or grace down to long-on
fired in and drives straight back to Kane who ends a decent over
comes down and nicely drives inside out but picks out cover
terrible full toss and Taylor needs no invitation to heave with all his might over long-on
quality stroke, dances down and lofts inside out one bounce to the extra cover fence
squeezes a full ball on off with an open face to point
comes down and places the push between cover and point
gets forward and defends softly to cover who is deep on the edge of the circle
short outside off and cuts away into the deep where Hira, who is an excellent fielder, manages to cut it off with a good dive
goes back and punches to long-off
on the pads and he works it through square leg
can't get the drive past the diving fielder at short cover
Nathan misfields as he tries to pick up and throw down the stumps from a work into the leg side

and gets the important wicket of Hamilton with his first ball of the new spell, a slower ball which Hamilton mistimed down to long-on as the bat rolled in his hands, end of an excellent knock which has set his team on the way to a possible upset
guides to third man and Elton's stretch may not have got him home if the throw had hit
outside off and he plays to deep third man
slower ball outside off, mistimes the drive and gets a thick edge through backward point along the ground
oh dear, they had a slip in and he edges the heave past Kane at slip, he was late to go and possibly a bit wide as well, heads to the third man boundary
backs away and slaps a short ball over point to the boundary
gets forward and works to leg
sweeps from outside off to deep square leg
tucked off the back foot behind square
stays deep in the crease and nicely dabs a full ball outside off through third man
top-edges the sweep outside off into the back of his helmet, pops into the vacant third man region
gets on the front foot and waits before square driving through backward point and it beats Hira's valiant dive on the rope
Southee starts with an accurate full ball which is squeezed into the leg side
another excellent ball in the blockhole on off and Taylor jams down on it quickly
driven to long-off
full toss on leg and flicked away to deep square leg
full toss on middle and he swings it away nicely out to deep midwicket where Hira is again diving to deny Zimbabwe a boundary
poorly directed and it's a full toss to boot, on leg and Taylor helps it on its way over backward square
nice and full outside off and beats Elton who drove loosely without moving the feet
again full outside off and Elton repeats the stroke, this time he gets an inside edge past the stumps and French cuts through fine leg
driven with excellent timing through the covers to give the fielder in the deep no chance, a poor full toss outside off
slower ball outside off which is tapped into the covers
another slower ball and Taylor is content to milk it into the covers
third slower ball in a row and Elton could see it coming, it is on middle and he waits before rolling the wrists on the pull behind backward square
terrible full toss outside off and Taylor doesn't time it to perfection but he doesn't need to as it sails over midwicket to bring up his 50
another wide full toss outside off and Taylor slaps it away with impunity to the cover fence
gets this to land on the pitch, full on leg and wristily worked to long-on
poor ball down leg and flicked to the left of fine leg where Mills dives and gets down well to stop it from rolling to the boundary
full toss on middle is heaved towards cow corner, Hira misfields and they come back for a couple, the throw might have had Elton in trouble had Bates collected cleanly
plays through the third man region where Ellis chasing dives to drag it off the rope
full outside off and he squeezes it to deep cover
full on off, backs away and slaps to cover on the edge of the circle
full toss on leg and he tries to work it through the on side but it hits the back of the bat and rushes off through third man, the luck going Zimbabwe's way tonight
excellent yorker fired into middle and leg and Taylor gets his feet out of harm's way before squeezing it out
top innovation from Taylor, fired into leg and he backs away and gives room to loft over the covers, the ball was outside leg
swings with one hand down to long-on
plays a full ball down to long-on
full outside off and beats the attempted slash
full outside off and he runs with the drive to cover
full toss outside off and he reaches to drag it into the deep, top over from Mills so far
dropped at long-off by Franklin, full toss on off, Elton came down and smacked it flat straight into the hands of the fielder and he couldn't take the simple catch
full outside off and they can only squeeze a single into the deep, excellent over by Mills at the death but he couldn't prevent Zimbabwe from bringing up their 200
